Q1 (04/23/2021): In the simulation tool set we plan to include hardware-in-the-loop components to emulate the various array configurations with actual hardware capability, we like to know if this is allowed or encouraged.
A: The focus is on the USG requirement for a robust modelling and simulation Tool Set which will be used to evaluate and establish&nbsp;expectation&nbsp;of future attack helicopter radar systems.&nbsp; The Tool Set must ingest simulated radar parameters, modes, radar data and target condition in a laboratory environment.&nbsp; The Tool Set can, as an added feature, employ actual radar data to demonstrate its capability. However, the articulation of simulated parameters and conditions in a laboratory environment must be the primary objective of the Tool Set.&nbsp;

